RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 1 4F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 4753. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPITFIRE SUZIE challenged outside EXOTIC GENTLEMAN nearing the lane, was roused briefly upper stretch and drew clear. CRYPTO MINER followed the leaders three wide and rallied clear for the place but could not threaten the winner. EXOTIC GENTLEMAN gained an early lead out from the rail and came up empty in the drive. CHARISMO was last away, went four wide and closed the gap through the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Spitfire Suzie
ENTRY.COMMENT: bid clear 3wd, roused briefly, drew clear

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 72. Claiming Purse 4700. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COWORKER stalked the pace three and four wide to move closer going to the far turn, bid into the lane and moved clear under steady handling. GIO SAMMY bumped with a rival at the start, was on the pace inside a rival while about the two to three path then could not go with the winner in the lane while narrowly holding the place. LITTLE TOE tracked the leaders three wide to bid into the far turn but was outfinished in the lane while just missing the place. SPEEDY FELLAR saved ground in good position to the far turn, angled three wide but lacked a final closing bid. OH SNAP was not a factor four and five wide. DRYSPELL bumped with a rival at the start, contested the pace three to four wide and weakened nearing the lane. RENVYLE trailed throughout.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 66. Claiming Purse 6300. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE NOVEMBER 19, 2022. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COLD AS YOU lunged then was bumped by a rival at the start, forced the pace outside TAPIT'S LADY throughout, rallied to bid through the lane and just held safe late as REMARKABLE CHARM challenged. REMARKABLE CHARM was in reach of the pace three to four wide, rallied five wide in the far turn then continued on to just gain the place late. DIVA'S DIVA saved ground in good position, bid through the lane but came up short late. TAPIT'S LADY broke outward to bump with the winner, was on the pace inside that one while from the rail and came up empty in the drive. YANKEE PRIDE stalked the pace three to four wide in good position but weakened. NEBRASKA RED weakened racing out from the rail. GUAPA CHICA was four and five wide in the first turn and was always back.

ENTRY.NAME: Diva's Diva
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, bid thru lane, came up short

ENTRY.NAME: Tapit's Lady
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out, bump, vied off rail, empty late

ENTRY.NAME: Cold as You
ENTRY.COMMENT: lunged, bump break, vied 3-4wd, rallied lane, held

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 4 4F Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 9400. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. Nebraska Bred Claiming Price $15,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JULIARD HONOR tracked the early leader three to four wide to bid into the lane, went clear and drew off under a steady hand ride. FASHION FACT tracked the leaders four wide and could not go with the winner while gaining the place late. OLIVIAN gained an early lead out from the rail, made the running to late in the turn and came up empty in the lane. ALWAYS A TIZ was four and five wide in the turn and continued on to miss the show late. LUCKY EVERY DAY failed to rally along the inside. HOT HABANERO was not a factor. FLAN was always back.

ENTRY.NAME: Juliard Honor
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked 3-4wd, bid into lane, ridden out

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Diamon Joe S. FONNER PARK RACE 5 1M Dirt CR: 84. Stakes Purse 20750. FOR NEBRASKA BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Purse $20,000-added. No nomination fee. $50 to pass the entry box and an additional $50 to start. Weights: Three-Year-Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of $9,000 at a mile or over in 2022-2023 allow ed 3 lbs., Of $9,000 in 2022-2023, 5 lbs. Maiden, Claiming and Starter races not considered in allowances. High Weights preferred on the scale. Total earnings in 2022-2023 will be used in determining the order of preference of horses assigned equal weigh ts. Closed Saturday, May 13 with 14 nominations.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PHLASH DRIVE was on the pace inside FOR REEL throughout, was headed by CALEB ON THE GO turning for home but dug in and rallied back through the lane to be up in the closing jumps. CALEB ON THE GO stalked the leaders four wide to bid through the far turn and edge clear into the lane but could not hold off the winner late. FOR REEL forced the pace outside the winner throughout and weakened nearing the lane. LITTLE BITOTHUNDER settled back off the pace two wide, moved up four wide but was not a threat. YAYASGOTMOREGAME stalked the pace in reach four to five wide and weakened. JUDGE'S BRIBE saved ground in reach of the pace and tired in the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Phlash Drive
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace inside, headed, came again late, up

ENTRY.NAME: For Reel
ENTRY.OWNER: Daniels Dwight L Doyen Larry Swartz Kent and Hurley Deborah

RACE.RACE_TEXT: FONNER PARK RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 61. Allowance Purse 8100. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUALITY BOW stalked the leaders while saving ground early, angled out nearing the far turn to move four wide, bid into the lane and ran down RETRO RITA through the final sixteenth. RETRO RITA was on the pace three and four wide outside rivals to bid through the far turn and edge clear into the lane then could not contain the winner late. EVIE saved ground back off the pace, moved up through the far turn but could not threaten the top pair. EXPECT THE BOSS failed to mount a bid three and four wide. BOUJEE BRITT was on the pace inside rivals and weakened nearing the lane. DISTANT HOLIDAY was always back. NOBLE PRESENT was not a threat three and four wide. ANGIE'S REVRAC was on the pace between rivals early and weakened going to the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Evie
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground, moved up into lane, no threat top pair
